			<header id="home" class="header">
				<section>
					<img src="https://der3syffk4l6q.cloudfront.net/in-the-lab/res/img.php/logo.png?v=jjlab-0.2.1115" alt="" loading="lazy">
					<h1 id="heading">Support the Show!</h1>
					<p>Super big shout out to all the people who have supported the show!</p>
					<p>Thinking of joining their ranks? Below are a few ideas for how you can support me as well!</p></section></header>
			<section>
				<h2 id="contents">Table of Contents</h2>
				<p>The contents of this page are organised into the following sections:</p>
				<div id="contents_div">Contents will go here (if you have Javascript enabled).</div></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="sponsor-on-patreon">Sponsor on Patreon!</h2>
				<p>If you can send me a few dollars a month via Patreon that would really help me to continue making content for the show:</p>
				<p class="indent">
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://www.patreon.com/JohnElliotV" title="Click here to see my generous supporters on Patreon, and maybe join them?">patreon.com/JohnElliotV</a></p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="click-affiliate-links">Click Through on Affiliate Links!</h2>
				<p>A great way to support the show at no cost to you is to click through on any of the green affiliate links on my 
					<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/equipment.php" title="Click here to see the lab equipment that I own along with affiliate links to buy. [Hotkey: E]">equipment</a> page before shopping at Amazon, eBay, or AliExpress. Even if you buy something other than the product I linked to I may still get a small commission. It&apos;s a great way to support the show without spending any extra money.</p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="subscribe-on-youtube">Subscribe on YouTube!</h2>
				<p>Another way to support the channel is to subscribe to the main YouTube channel:</p>
				<p class="indent">
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://www.youtube.com/@InTheLabWithJayJay" title="Click here to visit my main channel known as @InTheLabWithJayJay over on YouTube. Thanks very much for watching! And please remember to hit like and subscribe! :)">youtube.com/@InTheLabWithJayJay</a></p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="like-or-comment">Click Like or Comment on YouTube Videos!</h2>
				<p>It&apos;s always nice to get some positive feedback and your likes help me (and YouTube!) know what people consider quality content.</p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="sponsor-me">Make a Custom Sponsorship Deal!</h2>
				<p>As detailed on my 
					<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/sponsor.php" title="Click here to learn more about my generous sponsors. [Hotkey: S]">sponsors</a> page my friends at 
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://www.pcbway.com/" title="Click here to visit PCBWay.">PCBWay</a> send me free stuff in exchange for a mention in my videos, and my friends at 
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://www.siliconchip.com.au/" title="Click here to visit Silicon Chip magazine the venerable Australian electronics magazine and the publisher of the Mini Projects.">Silicon Chip</a> give me free advertising in the back of their magazine because they are awesome. If you have quality products or services of interest to the electronics hobbyist that it wouldn&apos;t  embarrass me to promote, 
					<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/contact.php" title="Click here to find my contact details. [Hotkey: C]">let&apos;s talk</a>.</p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="tell-friends">Tell Your Friends!</h2>
				<p>Letting other people who might be interested in the show know about it is a great way to support the show!</p>
				<p>You can use the short link: 
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://jjlab.net" title="jjlab.net">jjlab.net</a> or the longer link: 
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://www.inthelabwithjayjay.com/" title="InTheLabWithJayJay.com">InTheLabWithJayJay.com</a></p>
				<p>Or you could refer people directly to YouTube: 
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://www.youtube.com/@InTheLabWithJayJay" title="Click here to visit my main channel known as @InTheLabWithJayJay over on YouTube. Thanks very much for watching! And please remember to hit like and subscribe! :)">youtube.com/@InTheLabWithJayJay</a> or to my blog: 
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://blog.jj5.net/" title="Click here to visit my blog!">blog.jj5.net</a></p>
				<p>Or, perhaps best of all, you could refer people to Patreon: 
					<a class="external" target="_blank" rel="noopener follow" href="https://www.patreon.com/JohnElliotV" title="Click here to see my generous supporters on Patreon, and maybe join them?">patreon.com/JohnElliotV</a></p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="be-interested">Be Interested and Enthusiastic About Electronics!</h2>
				<p>Just taking an interest in electronics and being enthusiastic about electronics content is something that strengthens our community and promotes our cause. When our community succeeds we can succeed too.</p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="thanks">Thank You!</h2>
				<p>Thanks very much for your interest and 
					<b>I hope you enjoy the show!</b></p></section>
			<section>
				<h2 id="next">Where to from Here?</h2>
				<p>You made it to the bottom of the page, huh? Well done! I&apos;m a bit of a scroller myself. :)</p>
				<p>Where you go next depends on what you&apos;re interested in. Here are some suggestions:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>If you&apos;re enjoying my content you could consider 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/support.php" title="Click here to find out how you can support the show. [Hotkey: U]">supporting the show</a>.</li>
					<li>My 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/feature.php/new-book-teardown" title="Click here to watch the videos where I review new technology related books.">new book teardown videos</a> are quite popular, you might enjoy watching those.</li>
					<li>My personal favourites are the 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/feature.php/old-book-teardown" title="Click here to watch the videos where I review old technology related books.">old book teardown videos</a>.</li>
					<li>Visit the 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/channel.php/@InTheLabWithJayJay" title="Click here for high quality content on my main YouTube channel @InTheLabWithJayJay. [Hotkey: M]">main channel</a>, for all my high quality content including my 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/show-type.php/special-show" title="Click here to watch special shows which air on the main channel.">special shows</a>.</li>
					<li>Visit the 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/show-type.php/main-show" title="Click here to watch videos recorded for the main show.">main show</a>, for my main show videos, which include the 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/feature.php/electronics-project" title="Click here to watch the electronics project videos.">electronics project</a> and 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/feature.php/old-book-teardown" title="Click here to watch the videos where I review old technology related books.">old book teardown</a> videos.</li>
					<li>Visit the 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/equipment.php" title="Click here to see the lab equipment that I own along with affiliate links to buy. [Hotkey: E]">equipment</a> page, if you&apos;re interested in any of the equipment I use. If you&apos;re putting together your own electronics lab then I would certainly recommend checking this out!</li>
					<li>Did I mention that you can 
						<a class="internal" rel="follow" href="/in-the-lab/support.php" title="Click here to find out how you can support the show. [Hotkey: U]">support the show</a>? :)</li></ul></section></main>
